==English==
{{wikipedia|Binominal nomenclature}}

===Etymology===
Formed from {{der|en|LL.|binōmium}} + {{af|en|-al|pos=suffix forming adjectives}}. The derivation of {{m|la||binōmium}} is unclear. It was used by {{w|Gérard de Crémone}} in the 12th century. Suggested sources are the Latin {{m|la|nōmen||name}}, the {{der|en|grc|νομός||distribution, pasture}}, or the Old French {{m|fro|nom||name}}.[http://www.cnrtl.fr/definition/bin%C3%B4me] Compare {{m|en|binomy}} and {{m|en|binominal}}, as well as the {{cog|fr|binôme}}.

